<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khallimbloodhelm>KhallimBloodhelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/11/03 10:23 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.ptd.net/~twyst/images/ra.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on can i solo</span><hr size=1> Really depends on ur HP and weapons.  Yeah, u could probably solo one Hill giant in RM, unslowed and unsnared, but you'd probably be half dead afterwards.  Meaning that it would take you way too long to farm the plat.  Get a Truncheon of Doom, which procs 50% slow, a Silen Whip of Ensnaring, which procs snare, or Anklesmasher, which is a nicer weapon and also procs snare.  Another option is getting a weapon that procs fear, as well.  Pull out the ToD first, slow him.  Then the snaring whip, and then either the fearing weapon or just get ur high dmg weapons out and smack him down.  If you do this and keep a bunch of bandages on you, you can probably farm plat easily there.   <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:copperplate gothic light;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>They come like sacrifices in their trim, <br>
And to the fire-eyed maid of smoky war <br>
All hot and bleeding will we offer them.<br>
The mailed Mars shall on his altar sit <br>
Up to his ears in blood.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
