<br>
That said, OOT seafuries and giants in Bw will actualy give you xp and probably better loot if you can bring a couple friends including a healer. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirspliskin>Sir Spliskin</A> at: 3/13/03 5:31:10 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dobbobaggins>Dobbo Baggins</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/03 6:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on can i solo</span><hr size=1> don't waste time on ToD unless maxed out skill not worth it. I have ToD and by the time it procs they usually could be dead. i can kill anywhere from 3-4 hg's starting at full health. i'm 57 though. but at 57 i can bw to 80% ( fa1) so muchless downtime. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beornegarfrostwolf>Beornegar Frostwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/03 3:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question on can i solo</span><hr size=1> I can solo HG's with relatively little problems at 52 in so-so gear.  just take a healer with you to bail you out in case you get in trouble for the first couple, if you can kill them with no buffs and no heals, you're set.  Always have sow in case you get adds. One HG isnt a big deal, 2 in a row isnt terrible, 2 at once can get ugly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merkins2>Merkins2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/03 9:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hmm</span><hr size=1> bringing a healer with you isn't exactly easy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beornegarfrostwolf>Beornegar Frostwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/03 11:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Perhaps I didnt make myself clear.  I dont mean bring a healer with you every time you do it, just bring one when you want to test whether or not you can kill an HG solo. Once you know you can do it come back later and solo to your hearts content.  If you cant get one of your friends who plays a priest class to help you test this then they're not your friend. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thorinune>Thorinune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/14/03 12:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> thanks all for the advice I will try them out soon.  I was able to breeze through the Frontier Mountain ones and will now look to trying the Rathe Mountain ones.  Hoping it goes well, and putting my new gauss press to good work.<br>
